WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:11.516 --> 00:00:15.736 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:00:16.236 --> 00:00:17.206 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Hi, everybody.

00:00:17.356 --> 00:00:18.106 A:middle
Good morning.

00:00:18.256 --> 00:00:21.286 A:middle
My name is Rachel
Roth and I'm one

00:00:21.286 --> 00:00:23.556 A:middle
of Apple's User Experience
Evangelists.

00:00:24.746 --> 00:00:28.366 A:middle
Now this session is
not about monetizing.

00:00:28.876 --> 00:00:33.846 A:middle
It's about having a great
experience with in-app purchases

00:00:34.536 --> 00:00:36.716 A:middle
because a great experience
is what's going

00:00:36.716 --> 00:00:39.966 A:middle
to keep people coming back
to your app or game time

00:00:39.966 --> 00:00:41.836 A:middle
and time and time again.

00:00:42.746 --> 00:00:45.616 A:middle
Think about the last time you
had a really fantastic meal

00:00:45.616 --> 00:00:46.726 A:middle
at a great restaurant.

00:00:47.496 --> 00:00:49.666 A:middle
So it's a place you always
want to come back to, right?

00:00:50.846 --> 00:00:54.376 A:middle
So this is the bigger
picture of what it takes

00:00:54.416 --> 00:00:57.066 A:middle
to have a great experience
with in-app purchases

00:00:57.786 --> 00:01:01.466 A:middle
and today's session is all
based on the assumption


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:57.786 --> 00:01:01.466 A:middle
and today's session is all
based on the assumption

00:01:01.556 --> 00:01:05.296 A:middle
that you already have a
really amazing app or game.

00:01:06.756 --> 00:01:09.636 A:middle
Your app meets the
needs of your audience.

00:01:09.636 --> 00:01:12.566 A:middle
It's got a really
intuitive interface design.

00:01:13.046 --> 00:01:14.636 A:middle
It's been executed really well.

00:01:15.586 --> 00:01:17.326 A:middle
For game, it's just fun to play.

00:01:17.916 --> 00:01:20.046 A:middle
And there's really
no design secrets

00:01:20.046 --> 00:01:21.546 A:middle
or shortcuts around this one.

00:01:21.906 --> 00:01:23.746 A:middle
But I know that you guys
all have it handled.

00:01:24.346 --> 00:01:27.316 A:middle
So we don't have to dwell
on this for too long.

00:01:27.906 --> 00:01:30.606 A:middle
Now, if you're using the
freemium or the paymium model

00:01:30.606 --> 00:01:33.456 A:middle
with in-app purchases,
it's so important

00:01:33.456 --> 00:01:37.756 A:middle
that people can enjoy your app
or game without buying anything.

00:01:38.626 --> 00:01:40.866 A:middle
I mean, I think most of us
have had the experience.

00:01:40.866 --> 00:01:43.746 A:middle
You get a new app from the
App Store and you download it

00:01:43.746 --> 00:01:45.846 A:middle
and you launch it only to find

00:01:45.846 --> 00:01:47.516 A:middle
that you can't do
anything with it.

00:01:48.416 --> 00:01:49.476 A:middle
That's frustrating.

00:01:49.706 --> 00:01:51.326 A:middle
You need to make it
a purchase in order

00:01:51.326 --> 00:01:52.866 A:middle
to get some utility out of it.

00:01:54.116 --> 00:01:57.086 A:middle
It would be like if you bought
a mixer for your kitchen

00:01:57.086 --> 00:01:59.316 A:middle
and it didn't come
with any attachments.

00:01:59.316 --> 00:02:01.166 A:middle
You couldn't mix anything.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:01:59.316 --> 00:02:01.166 A:middle
You couldn't mix anything.

00:02:02.256 --> 00:02:03.626 A:middle
That would be really
disappointing.

00:02:04.176 --> 00:02:07.546 A:middle
And that's why mixers come
with a basic attachment

00:02:07.546 --> 00:02:10.776 A:middle
that you can use to mix and
see how great the mixer is.

00:02:10.816 --> 00:02:14.986 A:middle
And then you buy some additional
attachments for specialty tasks

00:02:14.986 --> 00:02:17.796 A:middle
like making bread or
some kind of pastry.

00:02:18.656 --> 00:02:21.146 A:middle
And that's what you want
to achieve with your apps.

00:02:21.406 --> 00:02:24.586 A:middle
You want to let people really
enjoy the functionality

00:02:24.586 --> 00:02:28.466 A:middle
and the utility, the
quality of your app,

00:02:28.466 --> 00:02:30.666 A:middle
and then you offer
them advantages

00:02:30.666 --> 00:02:34.676 A:middle
or additional functionality,
some advanced features.

00:02:34.676 --> 00:02:38.226 A:middle
And when you offer those
things, you want to make sure

00:02:38.226 --> 00:02:39.766 A:middle
that you make buying easy.

00:02:40.776 --> 00:02:43.996 A:middle
And I know this probably sounds
obvious but I'm not just talking

00:02:43.996 --> 00:02:46.986 A:middle
about sending the
transaction to the App Store

00:02:46.986 --> 00:02:48.056 A:middle
and getting a response back.

00:02:48.996 --> 00:02:50.686 A:middle
You want to make sure
that the decision

00:02:50.686 --> 00:02:52.906 A:middle
to buy something is really easy

00:02:52.906 --> 00:02:54.816 A:middle
for the people coming
to your app or game.

00:02:55.796 --> 00:03:00.896 A:middle
There's a lot of friction to
making that decision to buy


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:02:55.796 --> 00:03:00.896 A:middle
There's a lot of friction to
making that decision to buy

00:03:01.056 --> 00:03:03.456 A:middle
and a lot of it is
outside of your control.

00:03:04.586 --> 00:03:08.066 A:middle
But as app developers, you
want to eliminate any obstacle

00:03:08.306 --> 00:03:09.306 A:middle
to making that decision

00:03:09.306 --> 00:03:11.356 A:middle
to purchase something
inside of your app.

00:03:11.926 --> 00:03:14.976 A:middle
Make it easy as possible
because that decision

00:03:14.976 --> 00:03:19.136 A:middle
to buy is a fleeting moment
and there's many traps.

00:03:20.156 --> 00:03:23.346 A:middle
So one of the best
things that you can do is

00:03:23.346 --> 00:03:25.926 A:middle
to integrate your merchandise
into the experience.

00:03:26.966 --> 00:03:28.626 A:middle
I mean, people aren't
going to buy things

00:03:28.626 --> 00:03:30.206 A:middle
if they don't know
what you're offering,

00:03:30.266 --> 00:03:31.456 A:middle
if they can't see them.

00:03:32.356 --> 00:03:34.146 A:middle
I talk to a lot of developers

00:03:34.226 --> 00:03:37.476 A:middle
who create a really great store
section inside of their app

00:03:37.476 --> 00:03:39.426 A:middle
or game and then they're
really disappointed

00:03:39.426 --> 00:03:40.716 A:middle
because no one's going there.

00:03:41.066 --> 00:03:42.146 A:middle
They're not buying anything.

00:03:42.686 --> 00:03:44.546 A:middle
That's because people don't
know what you're offering.

00:03:45.216 --> 00:03:47.046 A:middle
It's kind of like the
difference of if I said,

00:03:47.046 --> 00:03:49.026 A:middle
"Do you want to buy something?"

00:03:49.846 --> 00:03:51.936 A:middle
Or if I said, "How would you

00:03:51.936 --> 00:03:53.656 A:middle
like a really great
drawing tool?"

00:03:54.266 --> 00:03:58.126 A:middle
And that's what you want to
help explain with your app

00:03:58.166 --> 00:04:00.186 A:middle
by putting the merchandise
out on display,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:03:58.166 --> 00:04:00.186 A:middle
by putting the merchandise
out on display,

00:04:00.876 --> 00:04:02.876 A:middle
integrating it into
the experience.

00:04:03.846 --> 00:04:06.366 A:middle
But when you're doing
that, I'm not suggesting

00:04:06.366 --> 00:04:08.906 A:middle
that you become a pushy
salesperson about it.

00:04:09.386 --> 00:04:12.606 A:middle
Nobody wants this guy following
them around saying, "Hey,

00:04:12.606 --> 00:04:13.676 A:middle
you want to buy something?

00:04:13.676 --> 00:04:14.706 A:middle
Hey, hey, hey.

00:04:14.706 --> 00:04:15.546 A:middle
You want to buy something?

00:04:15.546 --> 00:04:16.606 A:middle
Do you want to buy something?

00:04:16.606 --> 00:04:17.555 A:middle
Do you want to buy something?"

00:04:17.976 --> 00:04:20.296 A:middle
Every minute, and that's
what you're risking

00:04:20.296 --> 00:04:23.276 A:middle
if you're flashing a lot
of alerts or notifications

00:04:23.276 --> 00:04:26.486 A:middle
or crazy animations to try and
entice people into that store.

00:04:27.956 --> 00:04:29.876 A:middle
It's really about timing.

00:04:30.526 --> 00:04:32.676 A:middle
And with some apps, it's

00:04:32.676 --> 00:04:35.956 A:middle
about offering the right
thing at the right time.

00:04:36.416 --> 00:04:39.476 A:middle
Like at a restaurant, when the
waiter brings you the dessert

00:04:39.476 --> 00:04:40.556 A:middle
menu at the end of the meal.

00:04:41.606 --> 00:04:43.796 A:middle
I mean, you might not
even want dessert, right,

00:04:43.926 --> 00:04:45.706 A:middle
but it doesn't feel pushy
that they offered it.

00:04:47.116 --> 00:04:50.116 A:middle
It would feel pushy if they
offered it to you before you sat

00:04:50.116 --> 00:04:52.766 A:middle
down and while you're
eating your appetizer.

00:04:53.796 --> 00:04:56.136 A:middle
So you want to think about
what's the right moment

00:04:56.136 --> 00:04:58.486 A:middle
to offer something
to someone and do

00:04:58.486 --> 00:04:59.896 A:middle
that in a way that's
really thoughtful.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:05:01.196 --> 00:05:04.196 A:middle
Now with other apps, it's
about the presentation.

00:05:05.186 --> 00:05:08.376 A:middle
You want to think about a
really great window display

00:05:08.376 --> 00:05:09.206 A:middle
for a store.

00:05:10.066 --> 00:05:11.636 A:middle
I happen to be very partial

00:05:11.636 --> 00:05:13.516 A:middle
to the Apple Retail
window displays.

00:05:13.696 --> 00:05:15.736 A:middle
I'm sure that will come as
no surprise to you guys.

00:05:17.236 --> 00:05:18.616 A:middle
Now they do a great job

00:05:18.616 --> 00:05:21.306 A:middle
of showing off the
merchandise and drawing you in.

00:05:21.426 --> 00:05:23.596 A:middle
It makes you want to find
out more about the products.

00:05:23.596 --> 00:05:24.776 A:middle
It's really intriguing.

00:05:25.496 --> 00:05:26.976 A:middle
And that's what you
want to think

00:05:26.976 --> 00:05:28.586 A:middle
about with your app
or your game.

00:05:29.176 --> 00:05:31.216 A:middle
You want to integrate
the merchandise in a way

00:05:31.216 --> 00:05:32.756 A:middle
that feels really natural.

00:05:34.216 --> 00:05:36.736 A:middle
This is Paper by Fifty Three.

00:05:37.036 --> 00:05:39.586 A:middle
It's an Apple Design Award
winner from years ago

00:05:39.586 --> 00:05:41.906 A:middle
that is still a fantastic
example

00:05:41.996 --> 00:05:45.396 A:middle
of integrating in-app
purchases into their experience.

00:05:46.286 --> 00:05:49.806 A:middle
If you haven't used it, the app
is designed to capture ideas

00:05:49.866 --> 00:05:52.596 A:middle
through sketches and
diagrams and notes.

00:05:53.726 --> 00:05:55.656 A:middle
And like that mixer
in your kitchen,

00:05:55.656 --> 00:05:58.246 A:middle
they give you some basic
drawing tools for free,

00:05:59.016 --> 00:06:00.446 A:middle
your pen and your eraser.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:05:59.016 --> 00:06:00.446 A:middle
your pen and your eraser.

00:06:01.626 --> 00:06:02.946 A:middle
And you can see from
this example

00:06:02.946 --> 00:06:04.386 A:middle
that you can do tons with it.

00:06:05.266 --> 00:06:06.446 A:middle
But there might be an occasion

00:06:06.446 --> 00:06:09.306 A:middle
when you need a more advanced
drawing tool or a different kind

00:06:09.306 --> 00:06:13.746 A:middle
of line or texture and so that's
why they leave these empty spots

00:06:13.746 --> 00:06:16.226 A:middle
here where the advanced
drawing tools should go.

00:06:17.016 --> 00:06:19.626 A:middle
And that's like that
window display in the store.

00:06:20.216 --> 00:06:21.606 A:middle
It's putting them
out for you to see.

00:06:21.606 --> 00:06:24.026 A:middle
There's no question
what's available.

00:06:24.756 --> 00:06:27.536 A:middle
What they didn't do
is hide everything

00:06:27.536 --> 00:06:30.936 A:middle
in an arts supply store or
tuck it in a pencil case

00:06:30.936 --> 00:06:33.836 A:middle
that then you have to go push
open to see what's available.

00:06:33.836 --> 00:06:35.186 A:middle
That's creating friction.

00:06:35.326 --> 00:06:38.356 A:middle
That's expecting the
player, or your audience

00:06:38.356 --> 00:06:39.836 A:middle
to do work, to see what's there.

00:06:40.386 --> 00:06:44.956 A:middle
And another thing that
they didn't do is trick you

00:06:44.956 --> 00:06:47.106 A:middle
into thinking that you
already owned all these tools.

00:06:47.826 --> 00:06:50.486 A:middle
Because if you could see them
all but then when you tapped

00:06:50.486 --> 00:06:52.666 A:middle
on one to use it, it
told you that you need

00:06:52.666 --> 00:06:55.006 A:middle
to pay money just
to test out a brush?

00:06:55.436 --> 00:06:56.696 A:middle
Well, that would
be disappointing.

00:06:57.056 --> 00:06:58.916 A:middle
That's not a great experience.

00:06:58.916 --> 00:06:59.926 A:middle
It's a frustrating one.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:07:00.476 --> 00:07:05.016 A:middle
And that's why this design
is so elegant and so great.

00:07:05.456 --> 00:07:07.876 A:middle
It's informative
but it's not pushy.

00:07:07.876 --> 00:07:13.346 A:middle
Now next up, let's look at that
timing I mentioned earlier,

00:07:13.346 --> 00:07:16.176 A:middle
a totally different kind of
app, Bloomberg Businessweek.

00:07:16.916 --> 00:07:18.716 A:middle
And this is a business
publication

00:07:18.716 --> 00:07:20.936 A:middle
that has regular
updates, new content.

00:07:21.756 --> 00:07:25.366 A:middle
And without a subscription, you
can still browse, read several

00:07:25.366 --> 00:07:27.856 A:middle
of the articles,
browse all the headlines

00:07:27.856 --> 00:07:31.146 A:middle
and the introductory sentences.

00:07:31.336 --> 00:07:34.696 A:middle
Now if you tap on something
that requires a subscription,

00:07:35.806 --> 00:07:37.396 A:middle
they bring up the
subscription options.

00:07:38.496 --> 00:07:39.606 A:middle
It's like the dessert menu.

00:07:40.166 --> 00:07:42.466 A:middle
You're interested in
reading some of their content

00:07:42.906 --> 00:07:47.686 A:middle
so here's the information about
subscription so you can get it.

00:07:49.196 --> 00:07:51.776 A:middle
They're presenting it right
at that perfect moment.

00:07:53.346 --> 00:07:56.056 A:middle
They're making it easy for
you to get the subscription.

00:07:58.116 --> 00:08:01.206 A:middle
Now, they also have this
Subscribe button down here


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:07:58.116 --> 00:08:01.206 A:middle
Now, they also have this
Subscribe button down here

00:08:01.206 --> 00:08:05.066 A:middle
in the corner of every
screen and that's great too.

00:08:05.746 --> 00:08:07.506 A:middle
But having that in addition

00:08:07.606 --> 00:08:10.226 A:middle
to the integrated message
helps them reach more people.

00:08:11.256 --> 00:08:13.616 A:middle
So I'm not saying you
can't have a store section.

00:08:14.116 --> 00:08:15.936 A:middle
You just don't want to
make it the only place

00:08:16.026 --> 00:08:18.336 A:middle
that people can find
what you're offering.

00:08:20.706 --> 00:08:23.036 A:middle
Now this also works for games.

00:08:23.316 --> 00:08:25.456 A:middle
I don't know how many of
you have played "Smash Hit".

00:08:25.556 --> 00:08:29.266 A:middle
It's a really fun arcade game
that involves smashing things

00:08:29.266 --> 00:08:33.086 A:middle
as you might have guessed, very
satisfying after a long day.

00:08:34.056 --> 00:08:37.106 A:middle
The way that it works is
that it's an arcade game

00:08:37.186 --> 00:08:39.046 A:middle
and the more accurate you
are at smashing things,

00:08:39.046 --> 00:08:39.956 A:middle
the further you're going to get.

00:08:40.186 --> 00:08:42.316 A:middle
You progress through the
checkpoints unlocking them.

00:08:43.066 --> 00:08:46.076 A:middle
And they also offer a premium
version and they've a great way

00:08:46.076 --> 00:08:47.686 A:middle
of illustrating exactly what

00:08:47.686 --> 00:08:48.886 A:middle
that advanced feature
does for you.

