00:34:57.045 --> 00:35:01.126 A:middle
to impact everyone
and that's Ask to Buy.

00:35:01.126 --> 00:35:05.186 A:middle
So in the fall, you'll be able
to associate up to 6 people

00:35:05.186 --> 00:35:06.556 A:middle
in the household as a family.

00:35:07.176 --> 00:35:08.666 A:middle
And as part of this, we're going

00:35:08.666 --> 00:35:10.986 A:middle
to have a new parental
control called Ask to Buy.

00:35:11.826 --> 00:35:14.556 A:middle
And if it's enabled, this
means that a parent is going

00:35:14.556 --> 00:35:18.076 A:middle
to approve or decline any
purchases that a child makes.

00:35:19.036 --> 00:35:20.836 A:middle
So it's basically the
equivalent of this.

00:35:22.296 --> 00:35:23.046 A:middle
"Can I have it?

00:35:23.046 --> 00:35:24.166 A:middle
Please, please, please?"

00:35:24.946 --> 00:35:27.306 A:middle
But it's all going to
happen through your devices.

00:35:28.256 --> 00:35:29.386 A:middle
So here's how it works.

00:35:30.106 --> 00:35:34.606 A:middle
Today, when your app sends a
request to purchase something,

00:35:35.756 --> 00:35:37.986 A:middle
you're going to get a
response right back.

00:35:38.836 --> 00:35:40.456 A:middle
That purchased or failed.

00:35:40.456 --> 00:35:46.686 A:middle
Now with Ask to Buy, we're going
to check with the parent first

00:35:46.686 --> 00:35:48.036 A:middle
if Ask to Buy is enabled.

00:35:48.036 --> 00:35:50.156 A:middle
So you're going to send
the request for purchasing.

00:35:50.616 --> 00:35:51.916 A:middle
The child's going to
ask for something.

00:35:51.916 --> 00:35:54.336 A:middle
And then the App Store is
going to check with the parent.

00:35:55.196 --> 00:35:56.356 A:middle
So what does that mean to you?

00:35:57.986 --> 00:35:59.926 A:middle
During this time, you're going

00:35:59.926 --> 00:36:01.966 A:middle
to get a response
back of deferred.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:35:59.926 --> 00:36:01.966 A:middle
to get a response
back of deferred.

00:36:02.466 --> 00:36:08.216 A:middle
And then once the parent
accepts or declines the request,

00:36:09.246 --> 00:36:11.686 A:middle
that's when the App Store will
let you know whether it's been

00:36:11.686 --> 00:36:12.686 A:middle
purchased or failed.

00:36:13.976 --> 00:36:18.636 A:middle
And this deferred state can last
for up to 24 hours while waiting

00:36:18.636 --> 00:36:19.916 A:middle
for a response from the parent.

00:36:20.206 --> 00:36:22.816 A:middle
And if there's no
response within 24 hours,

00:36:22.816 --> 00:36:25.886 A:middle
it's going to default to failed
and the child can request again.

00:36:27.156 --> 00:36:29.876 A:middle
So what does this mean
from a design perspective?

00:36:30.976 --> 00:36:34.046 A:middle
Well, if you have
modal situations

00:36:34.256 --> 00:36:37.206 A:middle
where people are doing
purchasing, you need to shift

00:36:37.206 --> 00:36:39.226 A:middle
over to an asynchronous model.

00:36:39.786 --> 00:36:43.566 A:middle
Let's say your game offers
boosters at the beginning

00:36:43.566 --> 00:36:46.156 A:middle
of a level and a child
makes a request to buy one.

00:36:46.716 --> 00:36:50.516 A:middle
You don't want that child stuck
there waiting for up to 24 hours

00:36:50.516 --> 00:36:52.616 A:middle
to hear whether they
can have a booster

00:36:52.616 --> 00:36:53.786 A:middle
for the next level, right?

00:36:54.116 --> 00:36:56.486 A:middle
I can guarantee you, they're not
going to stick around that long.

00:36:57.746 --> 00:36:59.206 A:middle
So what can you do?

00:36:59.206 --> 00:37:02.156 A:middle
Well, you have to figure
what's going to be best


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:36:59.206 --> 00:37:02.156 A:middle
Well, you have to figure
what's going to be best

00:37:02.156 --> 00:37:03.766 A:middle
for your app or your game.

00:37:04.096 --> 00:37:07.036 A:middle
The important thing is that
you let people keep using

00:37:07.036 --> 00:37:08.926 A:middle
and enjoying your
app during this time.

00:37:09.636 --> 00:37:11.876 A:middle
So if a child's requested
a booster,

00:37:11.876 --> 00:37:14.746 A:middle
well you send the request
off for the parent to approve

00:37:15.146 --> 00:37:17.406 A:middle
but then you could let
them play other levels

00:37:17.446 --> 00:37:19.466 A:middle
or maybe they continue
playing the level

00:37:20.046 --> 00:37:22.746 A:middle
but without the booster and
when that approval comes in,

00:37:22.746 --> 00:37:25.536 A:middle
you bank it and let them
use it at a different time.

00:37:26.676 --> 00:37:29.746 A:middle
Another thing that you want to
think about is giving some sort

00:37:29.746 --> 00:37:32.116 A:middle
of feedback inside
of the application

00:37:32.466 --> 00:37:35.506 A:middle
so that the child remembers
that something is pending,

00:37:35.636 --> 00:37:37.466 A:middle
that they've already
asked Mom and Dad.

00:37:38.326 --> 00:37:41.846 A:middle
And so that you could update
the label on the button

00:37:41.846 --> 00:37:46.426 A:middle
to say something else or in the
App Store, we show a message

00:37:46.476 --> 00:37:48.926 A:middle
to help the child remember
that it's actually pending.

00:37:50.036 --> 00:37:53.266 A:middle
So if any people using
your app are under 18,

00:37:53.686 --> 00:37:55.956 A:middle
you need to start
preparing for this now.

00:37:56.926 --> 00:37:59.676 A:middle
That deferred state is
entirely new and you need

00:37:59.676 --> 00:38:01.416 A:middle
to make sure you're
handling it well.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:37:59.676 --> 00:38:01.416 A:middle
to make sure you're
handling it well.

00:38:01.796 --> 00:38:05.156 A:middle
Make sure people can still
