00:43:16.606 --> 00:43:20.076 A:middle
Help people focus on what's
still available to them.

00:43:20.076 --> 00:43:22.956 A:middle
If there's things they
can't buy, do prioritize

00:43:22.956 --> 00:43:26.086 A:middle
that in the UI, especially
with nonconsumables.

00:43:26.206 --> 00:43:28.346 A:middle
There is no need to keep
showing people something

00:43:28.346 --> 00:43:29.236 A:middle
that they've already bought.

00:43:29.436 --> 00:43:31.726 A:middle
They already own it.

00:43:32.136 --> 00:43:35.356 A:middle
Now in some cases, it may
not make sense to hide items

00:43:35.356 --> 00:43:36.576 A:middle
that have already been purchased

00:43:36.866 --> 00:43:42.636 A:middle
but just don't let them
be the star of the show.

00:43:43.056 --> 00:43:45.956 A:middle
And I think you're all aware
that it's very important

00:43:46.056 --> 00:43:48.336 A:middle
that you let people
restore their purchases

00:43:48.336 --> 00:43:50.406 A:middle
that they've made previously.

00:43:50.606 --> 00:43:52.776 A:middle
They could have made
it on another device

00:43:53.136 --> 00:43:57.036 A:middle
or they got a new piece of
hardware and it's important

00:43:57.036 --> 00:43:58.616 A:middle
that they can retrieve what
they've already bought.

00:43:59.596 --> 00:44:03.436 A:middle
This is "Brooklyn Magazine"
and they make it super easy.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:43:59.596 --> 00:44:03.436 A:middle
This is "Brooklyn Magazine"
and they make it super easy.

00:44:03.766 --> 00:44:05.276 A:middle
If you already have
a subscription,

00:44:05.276 --> 00:44:08.276 A:middle
well here's where to go to
start that restore process.

00:44:10.076 --> 00:44:11.456 A:middle
But they took it
one step further.

00:44:12.516 --> 00:44:15.636 A:middle
So if you were to tap on one
of these subscription options,

00:44:16.236 --> 00:44:18.376 A:middle
you get the confirmation
to subscribe just

00:44:18.376 --> 00:44:19.306 A:middle
like you would expect.

00:44:20.246 --> 00:44:24.916 A:middle
But if you hit Cancel, they ask
if you're already a subscriber.

00:44:25.476 --> 00:44:29.156 A:middle
And that's because there's
basically 2 reasons why you

00:44:29.156 --> 00:44:31.426 A:middle
might cancel subscription
confirmation.

00:44:32.126 --> 00:44:35.846 A:middle
One is if you changed your mind
about subscribing, of course.

00:44:36.126 --> 00:44:38.686 A:middle
And that's a much bigger
problem for them to tackle.

00:44:39.546 --> 00:44:42.006 A:middle
But the other is if you
already had a subscription.

00:44:42.396 --> 00:44:46.946 A:middle
So in this case, they're
helping get you back on track.

00:44:47.266 --> 00:44:49.306 A:middle
Now you all know it's
an App Store requirement

00:44:49.356 --> 00:44:51.766 A:middle
to make restoring available.

00:44:52.556 --> 00:44:54.596 A:middle
But a great experience
is going to make it easy.

00:44:54.596 --> 00:44:59.146 A:middle
All right, so one last
tip in this section.

00:44:59.486 --> 00:45:01.516 A:middle
And this is about notifications.


WEBVTT
