00:44:59.486 --> 00:45:01.516 A:middle
And this is about notifications.

00:45:02.206 --> 00:45:05.746 A:middle
You want to use them
thoughtfully and this applies

00:45:05.746 --> 00:45:09.086 A:middle
to push notifications as
well as local notifications.

00:45:10.506 --> 00:45:13.036 A:middle
Now you're not going to have
to notify children about Ask

00:45:13.226 --> 00:45:16.026 A:middle
to Buy, purchases completing
because the App Store is going

00:45:16.026 --> 00:45:17.006 A:middle
to handle that for you.

00:45:17.006 --> 00:45:20.746 A:middle
But you do want to use
notifications to let people know

00:45:20.746 --> 00:45:24.436 A:middle
about new content for
a subscription or maybe

00:45:24.436 --> 00:45:26.376 A:middle
in those dating apps,
they could let me know

00:45:26.376 --> 00:45:28.656 A:middle
if I have new recommended
matches.

00:45:29.826 --> 00:45:33.196 A:middle
Circa does a great job
with their notifications.

00:45:33.616 --> 00:45:36.336 A:middle
They serve up bite-sized
news articles

00:45:36.336 --> 00:45:38.566 A:middle
and they give you
updates as it's happening.

00:45:39.366 --> 00:45:42.436 A:middle
Now they're only going to send
notification if it's an article

00:45:42.436 --> 00:45:45.446 A:middle
that I explicitly followed
or if it's something

00:45:45.446 --> 00:45:46.986 A:middle
that they consider
breaking news.

00:45:47.946 --> 00:45:49.916 A:middle
And they're very choosy

00:45:50.336 --> 00:45:52.076 A:middle
about what they consider
breaking news.

00:45:52.506 --> 00:45:54.906 A:middle
Now this is not breaking news.

00:45:54.986 --> 00:45:56.486 A:middle
This is what I followed earlier.

00:45:57.166 --> 00:46:00.006 A:middle
Swiping on that notification
takes you directly


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:45:57.166 --> 00:46:00.006 A:middle
Swiping on that notification
takes you directly

00:46:00.006 --> 00:46:01.956 A:middle
to the article so you
can read all about it.

00:46:02.306 --> 00:46:05.096 A:middle
So they've made it really easy
for me to return to the content.

00:46:05.156 --> 00:46:10.186 A:middle
So you want to be really
thoughtful about the kind

00:46:10.506 --> 00:46:13.126 A:middle
and the number of notifications
that you're sending

00:46:13.506 --> 00:46:15.856 A:middle
because too many
notifications is just going

00:46:15.856 --> 00:46:17.106 A:middle
to annoy everybody.

00:46:17.656 --> 00:46:20.406 A:middle
And not only do you risk them
turning off notifications

00:46:20.406 --> 00:46:23.566 A:middle
entirely, they might just
wind up deleting your app,

00:46:23.566 --> 00:46:25.456 A:middle
if they get tired of
all the notifications.

00:46:26.426 --> 00:46:28.806 A:middle
That's not the experience
that we're after, right?

00:46:28.936 --> 00:46:30.876 A:middle
You want thoughtful
notifications

00:46:30.936 --> 00:46:32.896 A:middle
that will keep people
coming back

00:46:33.716 --> 00:46:35.566 A:middle
and make the app
feel more valuable

00:46:35.566 --> 00:46:40.236 A:middle
because suddenly there's
new content there.

00:46:40.536 --> 00:46:43.116 A:middle
Okay, so make sure that
you consider these things

00:46:43.986 --> 00:46:46.156 A:middle
after your customer's
pressed the buy button.

00:46:46.386 --> 00:46:48.766 A:middle
Completing the transaction
is super important.

00:46:49.296 --> 00:46:53.266 A:middle
Which brings us to the
final sort of stage

00:46:53.266 --> 00:46:55.296 A:middle
of a great experience
with in-app purchases

00:46:55.296 --> 00:46:58.256 A:middle
and that's measuring
and refining.

00:46:59.186 --> 00:47:02.046 A:middle
With all good design, it's
so important to iterate,


WEBVTT
